all over the city.

259
00:11:32.317 --> 00:11:34.194
[sighs]

260
00:11:34.236 --> 00:11:36.279
Fuckin' kids these days.
think they know everything.

261
00:11:36.321 --> 00:11:38.448
-Can you believe this shit?
-You're gonna need

262
00:11:38.490 --> 00:11:40.117
a lot of luck
to make this fuckin' work.

263
00:11:40.158 --> 00:11:41.758
-You know that. yeah?
-No. what I need is

264
00:11:41.785 --> 00:11:43.505
for everyone to be
on the same fuckin' page.

265
00:11:45.372 --> 00:11:47.374
Look. these.
these fuckin' dagos.

266
00:11:47.415 --> 00:11:49.751
they have their own
bullshit rules. right?

267
00:11:49.793 --> 00:11:51.920
Castellano is not gonna
sanction a hit against us

268
00:11:51.962 --> 00:11:55.006
unless he has absolute proof
Zaccaro's dead.

269
00:11:55.048 --> 00:11:56.716
Javits money means
way too much to him.

270
00:11:58.218 --> 00:12:00.178
How long you think
you can keep this up?

271
00:12:00.220 --> 00:12:02.347
[Jimmy] As long as it takes.

272
00:12:02.389 --> 00:12:04.433
If they can't prove it's us.
we're good.

273
00:12:04.474 --> 00:12:06.768
I'll tell you what.
how about we turn

274
00:12:06.810 --> 00:12:09.896
you two fuckin' clowns
over to the Gambinos?

275
00:12:09.938 --> 00:12:12.357
Yeah. you could do that.

276
00:12:12.399 --> 00:12:14.526
But Zaccaro was a made man.

277
00:12:14.568 --> 00:12:17.237
They may not be satisfied
with just us two.

278
00:12:17.279 --> 00:12:18.280
They may come after you.

279
00:12:24.202 --> 00:12:27.372
Fuck it. Give it a go here
with the cousin It. Thing.

280
00:12:27.414 --> 00:12:29.332
whatever the fuck it is.

281
00:12:29.374 --> 00:12:32.502
But if anything goes wrong.

282
00:12:32.544 --> 00:12:34.337
we will turn you
over to the Gambinos

283
00:12:34.379 --> 00:12:36.006
and take our fucking chances.

284
00:12:36.047 --> 00:12:37.047
Understood.

285
00:12:43.346 --> 00:12:45.182
Hey. Jimmy.
I just wanna thank you

286
00:12:45.223 --> 00:12:46.975
for what you done for me
back there.

287
00:12:47.017 --> 00:12:49.019
It means a lot. you know.

288
00:12:49.060 --> 00:12:51.480
And look. I know I was acting
a little crazy the other day.

289
00:12:51.521 --> 00:12:53.148
but I think
it's 'cause I forgot to take

290
00:12:53.190 --> 00:12:55.084
-my fuckin' pills. you know?
-Wait. wait. wait. wait.

291
00:12:55.108 --> 00:12:56.818
Are you fuckin' serious?

292
00:12:56.860 --> 00:12:58.820
Yeah. No. I'm sorry.

293
00:12:58.862 --> 00:13:00.822
You have gotta take
your goddamn pills. Mickey.

294
00:13:00.864 --> 00:13:02.592
'cause I am not bailing you
out of this shit again.

295
00:13:02.616 --> 00:13:05.952
Yeah. no. I'm sorry. Jimmy.

296
00:13:05.994 --> 00:13:07.829
Hey. look. let me buy
you a drink. huh?

297
00:13:07.871 --> 00:13:10.499
It's 10 AM in the fuckin'
morning. I don't want a drink!

298
00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:14.377
We have got work to do.
fixing your fuckin' fuck-up!

299
00:13:14.419 --> 00:13:16.379
All right. well then after.

300
00:13:16.421 --> 00:13:18.173
Jesus Christ.

301
00:13:18.215 --> 00:13:20.592
C'mon. let's find
Connor and Sean.

302
00:13:20.634 --> 00:13:22.844
Yeah. All right.
we'll find Connor and Sean

303
00:13:22.886 --> 00:13:24.012
and then we'll get a drink.

304
00:13:24.054 --> 00:13:25.263
Oh. shut the fuck up!

305
00:13:25.305 --> 00:13:27.265
[engine starting]

306
00:13:27.307 --> 00:13:28.558
[knock on door]

307
00:13:30.352 --> 00:13:31.436
Yeah?

308
00:13:31.478 --> 00:13:32.521
[Brendan] Open up.

309
00:13:43.365 --> 00:13:45.450
You do not need
to be checking on me

310
00:13:45.492 --> 00:13:46.692
if that's what you were doing.

311
00:13:47.911 --> 00:13:49.204
Thought I'd say hello. is all.

312
00:13:49.246 --> 00:13:50.872
May I?

313
00:13:50.914 --> 00:13:52.874
How'd you know where I live?

314
00:13:52.915 --> 00:13:56.086
I found out a whole bunch
of things about your new life.

315
00:13:57.546 --> 00:13:59.026
'Cause you're
a detective now. are ya?

316
00:14:02.592 --> 00:14:05.053
[scoffs]

317
00:14:05.095 --> 00:14:08.056
You know. when I was in prison.

318
00:14:08.098 --> 00:14:10.475
every day and night.
I thought about you.

319
00:14:11.268 --> 00:14:12.936
It was the only thing
that kept my sanity.

320
00:14:14.229 --> 00:14:15.564
The thought of seeing you again.

321
00:14:16.940 --> 00:14:18.942
I'm glad you're free.

322
00:14:18.984 --> 00:14:20.360
but things are different.

323
00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:24.322
Aye.

324
00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:26.032
'Cause of your boyfriend?

325
00:14:27.450 --> 00:14:30.412
I hear he's quite
an interesting wee man.

326
00:14:30.453 --> 00:14:32.581
A bit of a thief.
break a couple of legs.

327
00:14:32.622 --> 00:14:34.290
'Cause you and I have
never hurt a fly.

328
00:14:36.334 --> 00:14:38.253
He does what he has to.
to survive.

329
00:14:38.295 --> 00:14:39.588
He has not had it easy.

330
00:14:39.629 --> 00:14:42.465
but he's brilliant and kind

331
00:14:42.507 --> 00:14:44.134
and he gets me.

332
00:14:44.175 --> 00:14:45.427
Compared to me?

333
00:14:47.971 --> 00:14:51.099
I've known you and your
whole family my whole life.

334
00:14:51.141 --> 00:14:52.517
I don't have one anymore.

335
00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:56.021
And neither does he.

336
00:14:57.564 --> 00:14:59.316
He understands the pain of that.

337
00:15:00.191 --> 00:15:02.444
Does he believe
in something beyond himself?

338
00:15:03.737 --> 00:15:05.447
-Yeah. he does.
-What?

339
00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:08.992
Me.

340
00:15:10.660 --> 00:15:12.495
Brendan.

341
00:15:12.537 --> 00:15:15.206
I do respect you.

342
00:15:15.248 --> 00:15:18.668
But I agreed to hold the crate
for Ireland. not for you.

343
00:15:24.591 --> 00:15:26.134
Please. can you leave?

344
00:15:35.352 --> 00:15:37.187
Glad he's takin' care
of you. Bridget.

345
00:15:49.324 --> 00:15:51.660
Alright. Sean.
keep your eyes on the street.

346
00:15:51.701 --> 00:15:52.994
Keep the car runnin'.

347
00:15:53.036 --> 00:15:54.329
What I need you to do

348
00:15:54.371 --> 00:15:56.122
is to scare
the shit out of everyone

349
00:15:56.164 --> 00:15:57.600
and make sure they're
face down on the floor.

350
00:15:57.624 --> 00:15:59.084
I don't want
anyone looking up at me

351
00:15:59.125 --> 00:16:00.353
while I'm doing
my thing with the hand.

352
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:02.754
Yeah. okay. I got it. Jimmy.

353
00:16:02.796 --> 00:16:04.422
Yeah. I bet
they got a safe in there.

354
00:16:04.464 --> 00:16:06.067
-You wanna crack that too?
-No. I'm just gonna

355
00:16:06.091 --> 00:16:07.676
grab some jewelry
and get the fuck out.

356
00:16:07.717 --> 00:16:09.528
Are you sure? I mean.
that's where they're gonna

357
00:16:09.552 --> 00:16:11.155
-keep all the good shit.
-Hey. shit-for-brains.

358
00:16:11.179 --> 00:16:12.681
am I gonna have
a problem with you?

359
00:16:12.722 --> 00:16:14.241
No. no. I'm good.
Let's fuckin' do this.

360
00:16:14.265 --> 00:16:16.685
Good. All right. Everyone ready?

361
00:16:16.726 --> 00:16:18.103
Yup.

362
00:16:18.144 --> 00:16:20.522
And don't shoot no one.
All right?

363
00:16:20.563 --> 00:16:22.732
Fuckin' hand is
starting to stink!

364
00:16:22.774 --> 00:16:25.318
Let's go!

365
00:16:25.360 --> 00:16:27.529
[♪ Tenement Kids ♪
[by The Boys playing]

366
00:16:33.243 --> 00:16:35.036
Everybody get on the floor!

367
00:16:35.078 --> 00:16:36.555
You're getting fuckin' robbed!
Face the fuckin' wall!

368
00:16:36.579 --> 00:16:38.516
Don't you even think of
touching that panic button!

369
00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:40.165
Get your fuckin' face
on the floor!

370
00:16:40.208 --> 00:16:42.377
Head down!
Eyes on the fuckin' floor!

371
00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:44.212
I see those fuckin' eyes.

372
00:16:44.254 --> 00:16:45.774
I swear to God
I'll blow your head off!

373
00:16:46.756 --> 00:16:48.633
Keep those fuckin' eyes down!

374
00:16:51.761 --> 00:16:54.222
[Mickey] I don't want to see
any fuckin' eyes back there!

375
00:16:54.264 --> 00:16:57.058
Eyes down! Head down!

376
00:16:57.100 --> 00:16:59.144
Eyes down on the fuckin' floor!

377
00:16:59.185 --> 00:17:01.312
I don't want to see
any fuckin' eyes!

378
00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:04.648
All right. boys. let's go!

379
00:17:14.284 --> 00:17:16.786
[laughing. indistinct
calling out]

380
00:17:20.290 --> 00:17:22.459
[horn honking]

381
00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:26.755
[bartender]
Can I get you another one?

382
00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:28.047
If you insist.

383
00:17:29.799 --> 00:17:31.634
Kind of empty
in here today. huh?

384
00:17:31.676 --> 00:17:33.303
Yeah. it's the Javits Center.

385
00:17:33.344 --> 00:17:35.096
the whole
neighborhood's employed.

386
00:17:35.138 --> 00:17:37.599
I was making more money
when people were broke.

387
00:17:37.640 --> 00:17:38.850
[chuckling]

388
00:17:38.892 --> 00:17:41.186
Yeah. huh?

389
00:17:41.227 --> 00:17:44.147
Oh. Sweeney must be
licking his lips.

390
00:17:44.189 --> 00:17:45.648
all the security. construction.

391
00:17:45.690 --> 00:17:47.192
and labor going on.

392
00:17:47.233 --> 00:17:48.777
Ah. you know how it is. Glenn.

393
00:17:48.818 --> 00:17:51.654
[Glen] Yeah. What about
the Italians. I wonder?

394
00:17:53.156 --> 00:17:55.742
Dagos must be
getting a piece. no?

395
00:17:55.784 --> 00:17:58.244
Dagos are dagos.
It's the way of the world.

396
00:17:58.286 --> 00:17:59.829
Oh. you're right.

397
00:17:59.871 --> 00:18:01.623
What I don't understand.

398
00:18:01.664 --> 00:18:03.249
I mean.

399
00:18:03.291 --> 00:18:05.168
Gambinos must be losin'
their fuckin' minds

400
00:18:05.210 --> 00:18:06.711
the biggest construction project

401
00:18:06.753 --> 00:18:08.129
in the history of New York

402
00:18:08.171 --> 00:18:09.547
falls into the lap of the Irish.

403
00:18:09.589 --> 00:18:10.589
Yeah. go figure.

404
00:18:11.800 --> 00:18:14.135
Yeah. well. maybe there is a God

405
00:18:14.177 --> 00:18:15.637
and maybe he's Irish.

406
00:18:15.678 --> 00:18:17.222
No doubt.

407
00:18:20.850 --> 00:18:23.186
So. you seen any dagos
comin' in here lately?

408
00:18:24.354 --> 00:18:26.481
What're you talking about?

409
00:18:26.523 --> 00:18:30.193
Well. I'm just curious who
Sweeney's been dealing with.

410
00:18:30.235 --> 00:18:32.278
Is it that fat fuck
Frank Mancuso?

411
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:34.381
Or that other grease ball
everybody's talkin' about...

412
00:18:34.405 --> 00:18:35.657
John Gotti?

413
00:18:37.826 --> 00:18:39.346
Now how would I know
a thing like that?

414
00:18:40.703 --> 00:18:42.330
It's conversation. Ray.

415
00:18:42.372 --> 00:18:44.833
I'm just. uh. musing.

416
00:18:44.874 --> 00:18:45.834
Is that a word for you?

417
00:18:45.875 --> 00:18:47.710
Yeah. well.

418
00:18:47.752 --> 00:18:49.796
keep those kind of questions
to yourself. Glenn.

419
00:18:49.838 --> 00:18:51.756
if you know what's good for ya.

420
00:18:51.798 --> 00:18:54.634
Calm down Ray. I'm musing.

421
00:18:55.885 --> 00:18:57.428
Sweeney wants to see you.

422
00:18:59.430 --> 00:19:01.641
How'd Sweeney know I was here?

423
00:19:01.683 --> 00:19:03.184
[Danny]
It's three in the afternoon.

424
00:19:03.226 --> 00:19:05.106
You're a fuckin' drunk.
Where else would you be?

425
00:19:09.482 --> 00:19:10.900
Huh.

426
00:19:10.942 --> 00:19:13.236
Ain't easy being
a parent. is it. Ray?

427
00:19:18.867 --> 00:19:20.368
[sighs]

428
00:19:21.578 --> 00:19:22.954
This it? This is all you took?

429
00:19:22.996 --> 00:19:24.330
That's it.

430
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.207
We left the fingerprints
and got out.

431
00:19:26.249 --> 00:19:27.625
They had a safe
in the back. too.

432
00:19:27.667 --> 00:19:30.378
-but we didn't touch it.
-Did anybody see you?

433
00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:32.672
Did you fuck this up in any way?

434
00:19:32.714 --> 00:19:34.632
No. No one saw a thing.

435
00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:36.277
No. Mickey here scared
the shit out of 'em.

436
00:19:36.301 --> 00:19:38.469
Didn't you?
It was an easy score.

437
00:19:38.511 --> 00:19:40.281
You know. Boss. we could
probably go back some time.

438
00:19:40.305 --> 00:19:41.764
crack that safe if you like.

439
00:19:41.806 --> 00:19:43.391
The fuck you will.

440
00:19:43.433 --> 00:19:45.351
What about this? You want us
to fence it for ya?

441
00:19:45.393 --> 00:19:47.228
No. no. we're not
gonna fence anything.

442
00:19:47.270 --> 00:19:48.730
This is gonna stay
right here with me

443
00:19:48.771 --> 00:19:51.274
till this whole thing
fuckin' blows over.

444
00:19:52.066 --> 00:19:54.527
All right. what's your next
move there. Bobby Fischer?

445
00:19:55.987 --> 00:19:57.989
I figure we take
Zaccaro out of town.

446
00:19:58.031 --> 00:20:00.241
Where to?

447
00:20:00.283 --> 00:20:01.701
Near Boston.

448
00:20:01.743 --> 00:20:03.596
You know. make it seem
like he's fleeing to Canada.

449
00:20:03.620 --> 00:20:05.455
There's plenty of places
up there to hit.

450
00:20:05.496 --> 00:20:07.016
We'll leave first thing
in the morning.

451
00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:08.625
[Sweeny] Yeah. you know what?

452
00:20:08.666 --> 00:20:11.586
I got a friend up there
runs a place. Corktown Pub.

453
00:20:11.628 --> 00:20:13.338
Liam O'Shaughnessy's place.

454
00:20:13.379 --> 00:20:14.756
he's a Southie.

455
00:20:14.797 --> 00:20:17.258
Go up there. rob his place.
He'll help you.

456
00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:19.761
You mean rob his own bar?

457
00:20:19.802 --> 00:20:21.930
Fuckin' beat up his own mother
if I told him to.

458
00:20:21.971 --> 00:20:23.473
[laughs]

459
00:20:23.514 --> 00:20:25.350
-Go. on your way.
-Yes. sir.

460
00:20:30.063 --> 00:20:31.606
What do you think
their chances are

461
00:20:31.648 --> 00:20:33.858
-of pulling this off?
-These two?

462
00:20:33.900 --> 00:20:35.628
About as good as a fart
in a fuckin' windstorm.

463
00:20:35.652 --> 00:20:37.654
[laughs]

464
00:20:37.695 --> 00:20:38.964
Fart in a windstorm.
That's good.

465
00:20:38.988 --> 00:20:40.990
That's good.

466
00:20:41.032 --> 00:20:43.743
[♪ One Kiss To Remember ♪
[by Frank Fafara playing]

467
00:20:50.875 --> 00:20:52.543
Hey. Lina. how you doin'?

468
00:20:52.585 --> 00:20:53.836
Get the fuck outta my way!

469
00:20:55.838 --> 00:20:57.340
No. no matter how fuckin' late.

470
00:20:57.382 --> 00:20:58.484
even four or five
in the morning.

471
00:20:58.508 --> 00:21:00.426
he always comes home!

472
00:21:00.468 --> 00:21:02.553
Lina. I'm sure that
there's an explanation.

473
00:21:02.595 --> 00:21:04.681
No. John. he missed
our daughter's christening

474
00:21:04.722 --> 00:21:06.808
this morning! Nothing would
keep him from that!

475
00:21:06.849 --> 00:21:08.559
Here. Here. Have one of these.

476
00:21:08.601 --> 00:21:09.995
I just had this machine
imported from Italy.

477
00:21:10.019 --> 00:21:11.779
I don't care! I don't want
no fucking coffee!

478
00:21:11.813 --> 00:21:12.939
I'm nervous enough as it is!

479
00:21:12.981 --> 00:21:14.482
All right. listen.
Lina. come on.

480
00:21:14.524 --> 00:21:15.834
I ain't seen him
in a couple of days.

481
00:21:15.858 --> 00:21:17.298
But I'm sure
that he's gonna turn up.

482
00:21:19.529 --> 00:21:20.989
Is he with his goomah?

483
00:21:21.030 --> 00:21:23.092
Ah. come on. Goomah? What are
you talkin' about goomah?

484
00:21:23.116 --> 00:21:24.659
[Lina] Oh. shut the fuck up.

485
00:21:24.701 --> 00:21:26.452
I know. all right?

486
00:21:26.494 --> 00:21:29.455
I overheard him
talking to her on the phone.

487
00:21:29.497 --> 00:21:32.000
Well. that is news to me.

488
00:21:32.041 --> 00:21:34.669
Some Irish bitch he met
on the West Side named Erin.

489
00:21:34.711 --> 00:21:36.587
And I swear to God.
if he's with her.

490
00:21:36.629 --> 00:21:38.506
I will scratch
her fuckin' eyes out!

491
00:21:40.425 --> 00:21:42.927
Lina. go home. Okay?

492
00:21:42.969 --> 00:21:45.555
I'm gonna go look for him
myself. personally. all right?

493
00:21:48.516 --> 00:21:50.059
I got a brutta sensazione.

494
00:21:50.101 --> 00:21:52.520
No. come on. Don't say that.

495
00:21:52.562 --> 00:21:54.731
Come on. Don't talk like that.
Come on. Come here.

496
00:21:54.772 --> 00:21:57.650
I got no proof. but I can't
shake this feeling.

497
00:21:59.402 --> 00:22:00.862
I think he's dead.

498
00:22:03.156 --> 00:22:04.156
[door shutting]

499
00:22:06.909 --> 00:22:08.453
[sighs]

500
00:22:12.623 --> 00:22:14.709
-Where's your crazy half?
-Jeez!

501
00:22:16.919 --> 00:22:18.921
At the 596 getting soused.

502
00:22:20.757 --> 00:22:24.844
What are you doin'
sitting in the dark? Huh?

503
00:22:24.886 --> 00:22:27.889
[Bridget] There is something
I didn't tell you. Jimmy.

504
00:22:27.930 --> 00:22:30.850
Brendan Cahill
asked me for a favor.

505
00:22:30.892 --> 00:22:32.852
[sighs]

506
00:22:32.894 --> 00:22:34.103
What kind of favor?

507
00:22:34.145 --> 00:22:35.563
[murmurs]

508
00:22:37.440 --> 00:22:41.611
He asked me
to hold something for him.

509
00:22:42.779 --> 00:22:45.073
A package.

510
00:22:45.114 --> 00:22:46.114
A weapon.

